items.Overview: The Diamondback DB15 pistol is a compact AR-pattern firearm chambered in 5.56 NATO, designed to deliver reliable performance in a short-barrel configuration. Built by Diamondback Firearms, the DB15 platform is known for its solid construction, modern components, and compatibility with standard AR accessories. This example is offered in true factory-new condition and includes the original box, factory accessories, paperwork, a 30-round PMAG, and a 9-inch handguard.

items.I&P Summary: Diamondback Firearms produces U.S.-made AR-pattern firearms with an emphasis on modern manufacturing methods and value-driven reliability. The DB15 series has become a popular choice for shooters seeking a factory-built AR pistol configuration without aftermarket modification.
items.Condition Summary:

items.Overview: This Browning A5 Magnum Twenty is a Belgium-made semi-automatic shotgun chambered in 20 Gauge, manufactured circa 1967. Designed for magnum 3-inch shells, this lightweight yet durable platform is part of Browning?s legendary Auto-5 series, known for their long-recoil operation and exceptional field reliability. This example features a 26-inch barrel and retains its classic Belgian craftsmanship with well-preserved metal and wood finish.
items.Barrel Markings: Standard Belgian Browning factory rollmarks are present and clear.
items.I&P Summary: Belgium-made Browning A5 models are highly regarded among collectors due to their superior finish, hand fitting, and pre-Japan production quality.
items.Condition Summary: Metal surfaces retain the majority of their factory blued finish with only minor wear consistent with use. The walnut stock and forearm show light handling marks but no major cracks or structural concerns. Action remains clean with normal operational wear. Overall presentation is strong, particularly for a 1960s Belgian Browning.
items.Mechanics: The long-recoil action cycles smoothly with proper bolt movement and spring tension. Safety engages positively, and the trigger exhibits a clean break. The bore is bright with sharp internal consistency and no pitting.
items.Accessories & Paperwork:
No additional accessories or factory box included.
No manual included.
items.Notes For Buyers: This shotgun has undergone a visual and functional inspection only. As with all vintage semi-automatics, a professional cleaning and mechanical check is recommended before field use. Ideal for Browning collectors, upland hunters, or enthusiasts who appreciate the craftsmanship of Belgian-made Auto-5 shotguns.
items.Feature Highlights:
Belgium-made Browning A5 Magnum Twenty, circa 1967
Chambered for 3" Magnum 20-Gauge shells
Classic 26" barrel configuration
Very good condition with bright bore
Renowned long-recoil reliability
Highly desirable Belgian pre-Japan Browning production
items.MarketNote: Belgian Browning A5 shotguns?especially Magnum Twenty models?continue to see increasing collector demand due to their build quality, historical value, and declining availability in well-preserved condition.
